reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent quiet time playing and learning for 16 month old child
reviews.reviewText: Book keeps my 16 month old granddaughter focused and occupied for a long time. She is very intrigued with it. Excellent quite time learning!! Great for car rides too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very cute and suitable for a toddler!
reviews.reviewText: I loved my 18-month-old son's reaction when he saw this gift. I bought it with the intention that he could endure a long 12-hour plane journey. The only thing that disappointed me was noticing that in the summer section of the drawing, there were rays and rain instead. Additionally, the cloud that makes a sound had a slightly poorly stitched part with cotton coming out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Been looking for this for years!!
reviews.reviewText: I have been looking for this for literally decades! I remember playing with a book like this when I was a child. We called it a “quiet book”. It kept me busy but also taught/practiced fine motor skills. When my kids were little, I searched and searched and could only find expensive and disappointing versions. I was surprised to find this. Even better the price was extremely reasonable.Highly recommended!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So much activity !
reviews.reviewText: The quality is good and the variety of activities is really a hit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good idea, low quality
reviews.reviewText: I do think my toddler is going to like this book. It has lots of different activities and I like that you can unzip the pages.I didn’t like that I had to do all the sticky Velcro piece myself. They don’t feel very secure and I worry about choking hazards or losing the pieces. My alphabet and numbers also came incorrect. I got 2 A’s no S and no 7. You can tell the numbers come from two different sets of fonts and aren’t great. I will probably end up making my own if the book lasts past our first trip.
